\section*{Results}

We find that the diversity of tenure-track faculty is not increasing any faster than the the diversity of the American public. In a linear regression model across \Sexpr{prettyNum(nrow(subset(institution.models.df, dv==dv.var)),big.mark="," )} higher education institutions, we find that the percentage of under-represented tenure-track faculty increased by \Sexpr{prettyNum(coef(summary(linear.m1))['year.zeroed',][['Estimate']]*100, digits=2)} percentage points each year on average between the 2013 and 2020 academic years (p<0.0001,$R^2 = \Sexpr{prettyNum(summary(linear.m1)$r.squared, digits=2)}$). During that period and into the future, the U.S. Census protects that the percentage of demographic groups included in that percentage will increase by 0.2 percentage points per year. At this rate, U.S. higher education will never achieve demographic parity among tenure-track faculty (Figure \ref{fig:urm-faculty}: All U.S. Institutions).

Despite substantial variability between colleges and universities, sector-wide patterns are similar within common groupings of higher education institutions. Among Ivy+ Institutions, the percentage of under-represented tenure-track faculty increased by \Sexpr{prettyNum(subset(ivyplus.models.df, subgroup_value=="True" & dv=="tenured_un_tenured_black_latino_american_indian_alaska_native_hawaiian_pacific_multiracial_total_pct")$year_estimate*100, digits=2)} percentage points per year (p<0.0001). Within R1 universities, PhD-granting institutions classified with "very high research activity", the percentage increased by \Sexpr{prettyNum(subset(carnegie.models.df, subgroup_value==15 & dv=="tenured_un_tenured_black_latino_american_indian_alaska_native_hawaiian_pacific_multiracial_total_pct")$year_estimate*100, digits=2)}  per year (p<0.0001). Within National Liberal Arts Colleges, the diversity of tenure-track faculty is increasing by \Sexpr{prettyNum(subset(usnews.models.df, subgroup_value=='National Liberal Arts Colleges' & dv=="tenured_un_tenured_black_latino_american_indian_alaska_native_hawaiian_pacific_multiracial_total_pct")$year_estimate*100, digits=2)} percentage points per year (p=\Sexpr{prettyNum(subset(usnews.models.df, subgroup_value=='National Liberal Arts Colleges' & dv=="tenured_un_tenured_black_latino_american_indian_alaska_native_hawaiian_pacific_multiracial_total_pct")$year_pvalue, digits=1)}), faster than the rate of change in the population. As a result, U.S Liberal Arts Colleges might reach demographic parity by 

