\section*{Discussion}


\matmethods{
Observations of higher education institutions are based on  2013-2021 data from the Integrated Postsecondary Education Data System (CITE). This dataset includes all  U.S. institutions that are applicants in any federal student financial aid program. We annotate universities in the IPEDS dataset with their classification in the 2018 Carnegie Classification (CITE), the 2021 U.S. News and World Report classification (CITE, timestamped), and the Opportunity Insights classification of Ivy+ institutions (CITE). Institutions are included in the dataset if they reported at least one tenure-track faculty member during the observation period, if they are classified in any way in the Carnegie classification system. A total of \Sexpr{prettyNum(nrow(subset(institution.models.df, dv==dv.var)),big.mark="," )} institutions meet these criteria.

In this paper, we consider a faculty member to be part of an under-represented group if they are recorded within the IPEDs data as Black or African-American; Hispanic or Latino; American Indian or Alaska Native; Native Hawaiian / Pacific Islander; or multiracial. We estimate the total percentage of under-represented tenured and un-tenured tenure-track faculty by dividing the sum of faculty in these groups by the total number of tenured and un-tenured tenure-track faculty for an institution or collection of institutions. 

\subsection*{Defining Demographic Parity}
To estimate the percentage of currently under-represented faculty who would be required for demographic parity, we use 2017 population projections based on the 2010 U.S. census (cite). We then calculate the mean percentage of tenure-track faculty in the U.S. who were not classified as nonresident aliens between 2013 and 2021 and assume that this percentage will remain stable. 

To derive the proportion required for demographic parity in given year, we multiply the projected proportion of under-represented groups in the population by the  observed or projected proportion of tenure-track, U.S. resident, under-represented faculty for that year.

\subsection*{Institution and Institution-Group Projections}
For every institution and every institution group in the IPEDS, Carnegie, U.S. News, and Opportunity Insights datsets, we generate an estimate of change in the percentage of under-represented tenure-track faculty using an only least squares regression model in the following specification:

$Y_{pct} = Intercept + \beta_{Year} + \epsilon$

