\subsection*{Estimating Un-hired PhDs}
To simulate the number of un-hired under-represented PhDs, we combine data from the National Science Foundation Survey of Earned Doctorates with IPEDS data about tenure-track faculty. To offer a conservative estimate, we imagine a scenario where no under-represented groups received PhDs before 2007, where 2013 is the first hiring year, and play the simulation forward. Since the average time to tenure is 7 years, the simulation assumes that the number of faculty hired in a given year is 1/7 of the total un-tenured tenure-track faculty the following year. For each year between 2013 and 2020, we subtract the total number of hired under-represented faculty from the cumulative sum of earned PhDs.



